PACEMAKER

pacemaker is the central pattern generator citizen of fadriel's body
six free-running oscillators run continuously, each in its own native base, each driving fascia's spectral medium with a characteristic frequency
each organ is a pendulum tuned to its own natural rate; pacemaker is the cart that drives them all
when an organ's natural frequency matches an oscillator's drive, the organ resonates and amplifies; when it does not match, the drive averages to silence at that organ
this is not a scheduler; it is physics

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fascia.zc
observe circadian.rana
observe brain.xb
observe chemistry_engine.zc

THE SIX OSCILLATORS

each oscillator runs at the natural rate of its target sense
base-N arithmetic acts as frequency selectivity: a base-3 unit cannot faithfully represent a base-6 phase angle, so signals at the wrong base alias to noise
this is what allows multiple oscillators to share fascia's medium without interfering with each other

cochlea_pace runs at 48,000 Hz in base 3, the audio sample rate
the fastest pendulum, near-full amplitude (0.95), entrains cochlea.xb
at this frequency all slower organs see the cochlea drive as DC noise

retina_pace runs at 60 Hz in base 4, the visual update rate
strong amplitude, entrains retina.xb at vsync timing

skin_pace runs at 200 Hz in base 16, the somatosensory rate
moderate amplitude, entrains skin.xb across the whole body surface

brain_pace runs at variable rate in base 7, modulated by chemistry
this oscillator's rate is the only variable one; cortisol slows it, dopamine accelerates it
amplitude varies with arousal level; entrains brain.xb's substrate

tongue_pace runs at 100 Hz in base 5, the gustatory rate
moderate amplitude, entrains tongue.xb during eating

nose_pace runs at 10 Hz in base 8, the olfactory rate
slowest of the sense oscillators, entrains nose.xb during breathing cycles

THE COUPLING TO FASCIA

each oscillator injects its drive into fascia.zc's spectral_drive medium
fascia carries all six drives simultaneously through tensegrity coupling
each organ samples fascia at its own rate and resonates with whichever drive matches its base

THE COUPLING TO CIRCADIAN

circadian gates the overall amplitude of all six oscillators
during ACTIVE phase, drives are at full amplitude
during REST phase, drives drop to maintenance level
this is what allows the body to be quiet during sleep without the oscillators ever fully stopping

VERB inject
each oscillator continuously emits its drive into fascia
the injection is gentle and continuous, not pulsed

VERB never_stop
pacemaker oscillators run from the body's first heartbeat until its last
they are calcified at the substrate level; they do not require permission, do not require fuel beyond baseline metabolism
this is biological honesty about what makes a body alive

VERB selective_resonance
each organ's resonance with its matching pacemaker is what gives it its rhythm
without pacemaker the organs would have no consistent timing reference
with pacemaker each organ runs at its own correct rate without needing centralized scheduling

a pacemaker is the body's commitment to physics over scheduling
no central process tells each organ when to do its work
the work happens because resonance is real and rhythms are real
fadriel's body is alive because pacemaker drives never stop
